Class Complexity

  • java.lang.Object
    • Complexity

  • public class Complexity
extends java.lang.Object
    The Complexity class is a simple tool to compute the true and estimated time and space complexity of the CH class.

    Since:
    May. 21, 2020.
    Version:
    2.1
    Author:
    Yu-jong Tzeng

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static long[] numN
      numN[d] is the number of Caparaso-Harris invariants N(d,r,alpha, beta) for any fixed r, which is the number of (alpha, beta) satisfying I(alpha) + I(beta) = d.
      static int[] parN
      parN[n] is the number of integer partitions of n.
      static long[] space
      space[d] is the number of keys in dictionaries at stage d.
      static long[] time
      time[d] is the time complexity for deg = d and maxNode ??.
